---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import QuickSummary from '../components/QuickSummary.astro';
---

<Layout title="Stats" description="What each stat actually does for mid-game players in Last War: Survival and stat priority order.">
  <h1>Stats</h1>
  <p class="text-lg text-[#8a96b0]">Not all stats are equal. Focus on what actually helps your main squad right now.</p>

  <QuickSummary>
    <p><strong>Mid-game priority:</strong> Attack/Lethality → Defense/HP → March Size → Troop Load. Everything else is secondary until these are solid.</p>
  </QuickSummary>

  <h2>What Each Stat Actually Does</h2>
  <div class="table-wrapper">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Stat</th><th>Practical Effect</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><strong>Attack / Lethality</strong></td><td>Increases damage dealt. Biggest priority for your backline DPS.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Defense / HP</strong></td><td>Survivability. Extremely important for frontline tanks.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>March Size</strong></td><td>More troops in every march = more power in PvP, PvE, and rallies.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Troop Load</strong></td><td>How many resources you can carry while gathering. Critical for economy.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Skill-related stats</strong></td><td>Make your hero skills hit harder or last longer.</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h2>Where to Get Stats</h2>
  <ul class="text-sm space-y-1">
    <li>Hero levels and stars</li>
    <li>Gear (especially Mythic pieces)</li>
    <li>Research (biggest long-term source)</li>
    <li>Exclusive weapons and hero talents</li>
    <li>Base buildings (smaller but consistent gains)</li>
  </ul>
</Layout>